      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n#8210 enforces additional constraints to the type allowed in `cuda::device::warp_shuffle_*`, namely default contractible and trivially copyable.  \r\n\r\nWhile this is conceptually correct, the new constraints prevent using warp shuffle instructions with types that practically satisfy these property but where the type traits fail, e.g. `__half`, `__nv_bfloat16`, other reduced precision floating-point types, composition of them like array and structures. Enforcing such constraints prevent using them in many context, e.g. CUB.\r\n\r\nThis PR reverts the original behavior until we don't find a reliable way to prevent the problem.",
    "created_at": "2026-04-01T01:08:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-07T21:55:27Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-07T21:55:27Z",
